 'EPSTEIN NETWORK: Jeffrey Epstein operated a sophisticated trafficking network for decades despite an arrest in 2005. His connections to presidents, royalty, academics, and billionaires provided protection. His 2008 plea deal, arranged by future Labor Secretary Alexander Acosta, allowed him to plead to state prostitution charges and serve just 13 months with work release.',
 'GHISLAINE MAXWELL: Born into wealth as daughter of media mogul Robert Maxwell, Ghislaine used her high society status to recruit victims and provide legitimacy to Epstein. She was convicted on 5 federal counts in 2021 and sentenced to 20 years.',
 'POWERFUL ASSOCIATES: Epstein\'s documented associates included Donald Trump, Bill Clinton, Prince Andrew, Bill Gates, Les Wexner, Ehud Barak, and many others. Flight logs, photos, and witness testimony document these relationships.',
 'MODELING INDUSTRY: Multiple fashion industry figures facilitated access to young girls. Jean-Luc Brunel, who ran modeling agencies, was charged in France before dying in custody. The intersection of fashion, wealth, and exploitation enabled predators.',
 'IMMUNITY FOR THE RICH: The original 2008 plea deal included unprecedented provisions immunizing unnamed co-conspirators. Victims were not notified as required by law. The deal was later ruled illegal but too late to prosecute.',
 'ISLAND OPERATIONS: Epstein\'s private Caribbean island (Little St. James) provided isolation for abuse. His New Mexico ranch, Manhattan mansion, and Paris apartment served similar purposes. His private jets ("Lolita Express") transported victims.',
 'SILENCING VICTIMS: Victims faced threats, surveillance, and legal intimidation. Non-disclosure agreements prevented survivors from speaking. Media organizations were warned off stories. Private investigators tracked accusers.',
 'UNANSWERED QUESTIONS: Epstein\'s August 2019 death, ruled suicide, occurred under suspicious circumstances including broken cameras and sleeping guards. The full extent of his network and who else was involved remains unknown.',
